AB  - With the rapid development of information technology, intelligence and digitalisation have become an important trend in the transformation and upgrading of the industrial sector. Traditional inspection methods for hydropower plants, such as manual periodic inspections or maintenance strategies based on fixed time intervals, suffer from outstanding problems such as inefficiency, high costs, and lagging information feedback. For this, we propose a design scheme for an intelligent inspection system based on digital twin technology and apply it to the actual inspection work of a hydropower plant. The intelligent inspection system adopts advanced digital twin technology, realising the deep integration of the physical and digital worlds by integrating real-time operational data collection, online monitoring, video surveillance and predictive alarms. The application of this intelligent inspection system significantly improves the efficiency and quality of inspection in hydropower plants, reduces unplanned downtime, lowers operation and maintenance costs, and provides strong technical support for intelligent operation and maintenance in the hydropower industry.
ER  - 

