AB  - The trend and demand background of intelligent and digital development of pumped storage power stations have put forward higher requirements for the operation monitoring and fault warning of water turbine units. This article first analyzes the data monitoring requirements of water turbine units in pumped storage power stations and proposes strategies for warning design. Furthermore, the technical advantages of various measuring devices were compared at the hardware level. Subsequently, a comprehensive early warning system architecture for monitoring the status of water turbine equipment was proposed at the software level. Finally, a framework for comprehensive monitoring and early warning system of water turbine equipment status was constructed, and its functional requirements were clarified, providing corresponding technical routes for the intelligent construction of actual pumped storage power stations.
ER  - 

